# PR #10874: PS-69087 Phase 4: ExternalFileSystem fetch + download-to-FMS coverage
**Tipo:** test
**Branch:** `wip/adam/ps-69087-phase4-coverage` → `wip/adam/tfc-prep-non-tc-files`

## Descripción
Adds integration tests for ExternalFileSystem FetchFileFromExternalFileServiceAsync (#93) and DownloadExternalFileAndStoreInFMSAsync (#94). Extends AmazonS3IntegrationTests and AzureBlobIntegrationTests. Updates coverage-progress.md and PS-69087-fileshare-methods.playlist.

Made with [Cursor](https://cursor.com)

## Feedback de reviewers
[COMMENTED por @copilot-pull-request-reviewer[bot]]: ## Pull request overview

Adds Phase 4 PS-69087 integration test coverage for external-file retrieval paths by exercising `ExternalFileSystem.FetchFileFromExternalFileServiceAsync` (via reflection) and `ExternalFileSystem.DownloadExternalFileAndStoreInFMSAsync` (end-to-end via foreground job execution), with supporting tracking updates in the PS-69087 coverage docs/artifacts.

**Changes:**
- Extend `AmazonS3IntegrationTests` and `AzureBlobIntegrationTests` with new integration tests covering external fetch and download-to-FMS flows.
- Update Phase 4 progress tracking notes in `coverage-progress.md`.
- Add/update a PS-69087 test playlist file intended to target the relevant test classes.

### Reviewed changes

Copilot reviewed 4 out of 4 changed files in this pull request and generated 6 comments.

| File | Description |
| ---- | ----------- |
| docs/temp/tfs-prep-non-tc-files/PS-69087-fileshare-methods.playlist | Adds a playlist file for selecting PS-69087-related tests (currently mismatched with Phase 4 content per review comments). |
| docs/temp/tfs-prep-non-tc-files/coverage-progress.md | Updates Phase 4 progress tracker and adds Phase 4 implementation notes (includes a BOM + playlist mismatch per review comments). |
| Core/Tests/ProjectSight.Tests.ParallelIntegrationTests/ExternalFileService/AzureBlobIntegrationTests.cs | Adds Azure Blob integration tests covering external fetch and download-to-FMS behavior plus helper methods. |
| Core/Tests/ProjectSight.Tests.ParallelIntegrationTests/ExternalFileService/AmazonS3IntegrationTests.cs | Adds S3 integration tests covering external fetch and download-to-FMS behavior plus helper methods. |
[Comentario en Core/Tests/ProjectSight.Tests.ParallelIntegrationTests/ExternalFileService/AmazonS3IntegrationTests.cs:14 por @Copilot]: This test class mutates the global Ignition `Control.ExternalFileServiceType` via `ChangeAzureBlobStorage(false)`, but this project runs tests in parallel at class level. That can race with other classes (including the Azure tests) and make outcomes nondeterministic depending on execution order/timing. Prefer making these tests non-parallel (e.g., add `[DoNotParallelize]` and ensure state is restored) or move them to the non-parallel integration test project if they require shared/global configuration changes.
[Comentario en Core/Tests/ProjectSight.Tests.ParallelIntegrationTests/ExternalFileService/AzureBlobIntegrationTests.cs:28 por @Copilot]: `CustomTestCleanupAsync` should call `await base.CustomTestCleanupAsync()` last (per integration test conventions). Calling base cleanup first means the suite’s standard cleanup runs while Azure Blob storage is still enabled, and the flag reset happens after cleanup (and may be skipped if cleanup throws). Reorder this method so Azure storage is reset before the base cleanup, and call base cleanup last (ideally in a `finally`).
[Comentario en Core/Tests/ProjectSight.Tests.ParallelIntegrationTests/ExternalFileService/AzureBlobIntegrationTests.cs:14 por @Copilot]: This class toggles the global Ignition `Control.ExternalFileServiceType` (Azure on/off) in a test assembly that is explicitly parallelized at class level. That can interfere with other concurrently running classes that depend on the configured external file service. Consider marking this class `[DoNotParallelize]` (and restoring state robustly) or moving these tests to the non-parallel integration test project if they must mutate shared/global configuration.
[Comentario en docs/temp/tfs-prep-non-tc-files/PS-69087-fileshare-methods.playlist:23 por @Copilot]: The file header/comment says “PS-69087 Phase 5” and the included classes are drawing/PDF tests, but this PR (Phase 4) claims to add ExternalFileSystem external-file-service coverage and update this playlist accordingly. If this playlist is meant to drive Phase 4 coverage, it should include the external file service integration test classes instead (e.g., `...ExternalFileService.AmazonS3IntegrationTests` and `...ExternalFileService.AzureBlobIntegrationTests`).
[Comentario en docs/temp/tfs-prep-non-tc-files/coverage-progress.md:1 por @Copilot]: This file now starts with a UTF-8 BOM (the invisible character before `#`). The other markdown files in this folder don’t use a BOM, and it can cause noisy diffs/tooling quirks. Please remove the BOM so the first character is `#`.
[Comentario en docs/temp/tfs-prep-non-tc-files/coverage-progress.md:152 por @Copilot]: The Phase 4 notes claim the playlist includes the ExternalFileService test classes, but the added `PS-69087-fileshare-methods.playlist` currently lists drawing/PDF classes instead. Update either the playlist or this note so they match; otherwise the tracker will point at the wrong tests.

